---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Timber Sleeper Retaining Walls Pakenham | Treated Pine & Hardwood"
  description="Timber sleeper retaining walls for Pakenham, Officer, Berwick. Treated pine and hardwood (red gum, ironbark). 15–40 year lifespan, $250–$400/m² installed. Free quote — (03) 9003 0223."
  canonical="https://pakenhamretainingwalls.com.au/services/timber-retaining-walls/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Timber Sleeper Walls</span>
      <h1>Timber sleeper <span class="accent">retaining walls</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The most economical option for residential retaining. Done right, a treated pine
        wall lasts 15&ndash;25 years; a hardwood wall lasts 30&ndash;40+ years.
        Done wrong, either fails in five.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Timber options</span>
      <h2>Three timber wall systems &mdash; pick by lifespan and budget.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>1. H4 treated pine sleepers</h3>
        <p>
          The most common choice. CCA-treated pine sleepers, 200&times;75mm or 200&times;100mm,
          slid between hot-dipped galvanised C-section posts cored into concrete.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $250&ndash;$320/m&sup2; installed</li>
          <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> 15&ndash;25 years</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> walls under 1.2m, garden beds, fence-line walls, budget-driven jobs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">2. H5 in-ground treated pine</h3>
        <p>
          Heavier preservative treatment for in-ground contact. Worth the extra cost on damp
          sites or where you want closer to a 25&ndash;30 year lifespan.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $290&ndash;$360/m&sup2; installed</li>
          <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> 25&ndash;30 years</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> wet ground, walls on the south side of the house, longer-life budget jobs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">3. Australian hardwood (red gum, ironbark, jarrah)</h3>
        <p>
          Genuine hardwood sleepers. Heavy, dense, naturally rot-resistant. Looks
          beautiful and lasts a generation.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $360&ndash;$450/m&sup2; installed</li>
          <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> 30&ndash;40+ years</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> feature walls in the front yard, premium homes, "build it once" jobs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What we won&rsquo;t do</h3>
        <p>
          We don&rsquo;t use H3-rated pine for retaining (only above ground), we don&rsquo;t skip the
          drainage zone to save $80, and we don&rsquo;t use star pickets or treated pine posts.
          Galvanised steel posts only. There&rsquo;s a reason cheap walls fail.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other wall types.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/concrete-sleeper-walls/"><h3>Concrete sleeper</h3><p>50+ year lifespan, ideal for taller walls.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/block-retaining-walls/"><h3>Block / masonry</h3><p>Premium look, long lifespan.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/excavation-earthworks/"><h3>Earthworks</h3><p>Cut-and-fill, drainage, levelling.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/"><h3>Back to home</h3><p>Pakenham retaining walls overview.</p><span class="svc-link">Home &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free timber wall quote.</h2>
        <p>Site visit, fixed price, written quote within 48 hours.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Quote online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
